name: gene product is a member of
species specific
description: X speciesSpecific Y means that Y is a general phenomena, like a pathway, and X is the version that appears in a species. X should state which species with RO:0002162 (in taxon)

name: has left-to-right reaction
description: X ltr Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a left-to-right reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: has right-to-left reaction
description: X rtl Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a right-to-left reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: has bi-directional reaction
description: X bi Y means reaction X of undetermined direction has a bidirectional reaction Y. Relevant for Rhea.

name: is conjugate base of
description: X is conjugate base of Y typically means that X is a deprotonated form of Y

name: is conjugate acid of
description: X is conjugate acid of Y typically means that Y is a protonated form of X

name: is enantiomer of
description: X and Y are in an enantiomeric relationship if flipping all stereocenters of X results in Y

name: is tautomer of
description: X and Y are tautomers if they are different realizations of the resonance structure of the same molecule

name: has parent hydride
description: X has parent hydride Y if the substituents on X are replaced with hydrogens. E.g., SbCl3 has parent hydride SbH3

name: has functional parent
description: X has functional parent Y if X is a derivative (e.g., a salt) of Y. E.g., bepridil hydrochloride has functional parent bepridil

name: has origin
description: Related to sequences

name: is substituent group from
description: connects a group to its chemical entity (e.g., carboyxylic acid group to acetate)

name: has citation
description: connects any entity to a document (e.g., with a pubmed, doi, pmc, or arxiv identifier)

name: causes side effect
description: connects any entity a side effect that it causes. For example, VO:0000112 (Tripedia) induces the side effect  HP:0002013 (Vomiting)

name: pathogen has host
description: connects a pathogen (NCBITaxon) to a host (NCBITaxon)

name: vaccine has gene engineering
description: connects a vaccine (VO) to a gene that has been engineered. Most applicable to OMVs, Nanosponges, and nanolipoparticles (NLP).

name: has intervention
description: connects a clinical trial to an intervention it investigates

name: has condition
description: connects a clinical trial to a condition it investigates

name: has platform
description: connects a vaccine to its platform

name: mentioned in
description: connects any entity to an article in which it's mentioned, e.g., extracted from NER

name: annotated with
description: connects an article to a term it was annotated with (i.e. pubmed annotated with MeSH term)

name: related trial
description: connects a related trial registered in a different registry

name: prevents infection
description: Sibling relationship to vo:0001011 (immunizes against disease)

name: pathogen defines vaccine class
description: A relationship where the domain is a taxon and the range is a vaccine family. E.g., Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (ncbitaxon:2697049) is the pathogen that defines vaccine class COVID-19 vaccine (VO:0004908). Sort of an inverse of VO:0003355, but more specific

name: vector vaccine uses pathogen as vector
description: connects a vaccine platform that is a vector vaccine to a pathogen that it uses as a vector
